The paper deals with the discrepancy of random set systems, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The use of LP duality and counting arguments suggests a connection to algorithms and complexity theory, which are typically covered in cs.DS and cs.CC. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the random set system, and graph theory (cs.GT) in the partial coloring method. Finally, probability theory (cs.PR) is used in the random setting of the problem.
